fields.description: The NGAD program is a sixth generation fighter currently in development by the US Air Force, it is expected to enter service after 2030 and will replace the F-22 in frontline service. Very few information is available, but it is expected that it will be stealthier with long range, advanced weapons and variable cycle engines

The Tempest FCAS is a sixth-generation fighter in development by BAE Systems in partnership with Alenia and Saab, it is expected to serve as a replacement for the UK's and Italy's Eurofighter Typhoon, and maybe also Sweden's Gripen

The New Generation Fighter is a sixth-generation multirole fighter in development by France's Dassault Aviation and Germany's Airbus Defence and Space in partnership with Safran, MTU, Thales, Indra and MBDA. It will replace French Rafales, German and Spanish Typhoons from 2040.

fields.contenu: Wow, that means I'm going to retire at 25 ! That's great, and depressing at the same time...
